race.comment: RUBY SEVENS (5) made it back-to-back wins when successful last start over 1000m at Emerald at 50 level. Has an awkward gate but she's speedy and will carry just 52kg this grade with the 3kg claim atop. Has more upside than most of these and can win again. DISCOVERED GOLD (2) rates a threat off her narrow defeat here as favourite in a CL1. Jumps from a wide barrier but should present at peak and the winkers are on again. A long tail. SUPER SLICK (8) has been freshened and her bush form might see her fill the next slot. LOVE MY LOUIS (9) was an easy winner two back at a non-TAB but this is a step-up for here as well.
